OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 21 Jun to Tue 30 Jun
OL,6,FProbably a north-south split at the
OL,7,Fstart of this period. In the north,
OL,8,Fchangeable and often rather cloudy
OL,9,Fwith showers or some longer spells of
OL,10,Frain, perhaps heavy at times, and
OL,11,Ftemperatures near normal. In the
OL,12,Fsouth, mainly fine and dry with
OL,13,Ftemperatures well above normal, albeit
OL,14,Fwith a small risk of a few showers or
OL,15,Fthunderstorms at times. Into late
OL,16,FJune, high pressure may begin to build
OL,17,Fwith conditions becoming more widely
OL,18,Fdry and settled. Temperatures are
OL,19,Flikely to be above normal for many
OL,20,Fareas.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16302
