PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1781614115
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 30 Jun to Tue 14 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure is expected to lie close
OL,7,Fto the UK at the start of this period,
OL,8,Fbringing mainly dry, settled weather.
OL,9,FTemperatures will likely be above
OL,10,Fnormal, with the potential for hot
OL,11,Fconditions, accompanied by occasional
OL,12,Fthunderstorms, especially in the
OL,13,Fsouth. Into July, the influence of
OL,14,Fhigh pressure may weaken or shift more
OL,15,Fto the north of the UK. This leads to
OL,16,Fan increasing chance of periods of
OL,17,Funsettled weather, either in the form
OL,18,Fof Atlantic low pressure systems
OL,19,Fmoving in from the west or
OL,20,Fthunderstorms developing more widely
OL,21,Fcompared to the start of the period.
OL,22,FTemperatures will probably return
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fcloser to normal too, although some
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fwarm and humid spells remain likely at
OL,25,Ftimes.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
